                {"src": "ellicott", "attr": "Ellicott's Commentary", "html": "<p>We have seen how the writer approached the subject which is the chief theme of this last division. The coming of the Lord draws nigh. In the midst of dangers and judgments God's righteous servant shall live by his steadfast faith. Faith is the steadfast assurance of things hoped for, and the \"test\" or demonstration of things not seen — not a mere feeling, but the ground on which the unseen becomes real to the soul.</p>"},
